Maybe I was nervous.

37:32.193 --> 37:33.567
Uh...
[stammers]

37:33.651 --> 37:35.943
You didn't want me to grow up.

37:41.151 --> 37:43.151
What?

37:43.235 --> 37:45.609
Because you love me.

37:45.692 --> 37:48.068
Of course I loved you,
sweetheart.

37:48.151 --> 37:51.526
But you didn't want me
to grow up.

37:51.609 --> 37:54.318
What's this about?

37:54.401 --> 37:57.442
[Bridget] You wouldn't teach me
to drive because you

37:57.526 --> 38:00.193
wanted to protect you--
not me, you.

38:00.276 --> 38:03.151
And you wouldn't let Mom die
the way she wanted to--

38:03.235 --> 38:07.026
needed to--because you
didn't want to hurt yourself.

38:07.110 --> 38:10.943
You were protecting you.

38:11.026 --> 38:14.651
If I want to be happy,
I have to move away.

38:14.734 --> 38:17.943
I have to get
away from you.

38:18.026 --> 38:19.567
You'll never let me be happy.

38:19.651 --> 38:22.609
And it's not your fault.

38:22.692 --> 38:24.734
It's not.
And I know you're hurt.

38:24.818 --> 38:27.110
[voice breaking]
And I know you try.

38:27.193 --> 38:31.526
But you can't touch anything
without fucking breaking it.

38:31.609 --> 38:33.360
And I'm gonna get married.

38:33.442 --> 38:35.567
I'm gonna have a family.

38:35.651 --> 38:37.651
I want a life.
I want a future.

38:37.734 --> 38:39.943
And you have
to let me go, okay?

38:40.026 --> 38:43.442
Can you do that?
Can you let me go?

38:43.526 --> 38:46.609
Let you go?

38:46.692 --> 38:48.401
You're my daughter.

38:50.193 --> 38:53.151
And you're my dad...
forever.

38:53.235 --> 38:56.193
♪ dramatic music ♪

38:56.276 --> 39:00.943
♪♪♪

39:07.276 --> 39:09.068
[sniffles]

39:09.151 --> 39:10.776
[snorts]

39:10.859 --> 39:15.776
♪♪♪

39:16.943 --> 39:19.734
[Justine]
We can't keep doing this.

39:19.818 --> 39:21.609
We have to say good-bye.

39:21.692 --> 39:26.651
♪♪♪

39:26.734 --> 39:29.901
[indistinct chatter]

39:50.567 --> 39:53.734
[indistinct chatter,
car horn honks]

39:55.318 --> 39:58.318
♪♪♪

39:58.401 --> 40:00.776
[siren wailing]

40:00.859 --> 40:03.276
[girls chattering]

40:03.360 --> 40:08.526
♪♪♪

40:19.360 --> 40:21.276
[thud]

40:21.360 --> 40:24.193
[car horns honking]

40:28.068 --> 40:30.692
[cell phone beeps,
camera shutter clicks]

40:30.776 --> 40:33.859
♪♪♪

40:33.943 --> 40:36.818
Free in a way you'll never be.

40:36.901 --> 40:42.026
♪♪♪

41:13.943 --> 41:15.567
[man] Whoa.

41:15.651 --> 41:18.526
Hey. Hey, buddy.
Buddy, are you okay?

41:18.609 --> 41:20.110
It's all right.
It's okay. It's all right.

41:20.193 --> 41:21.484
Come on. Come on, let's get
to your feet.

41:21.567 --> 41:22.818
Get to your feet.
You're gonna be fine.

41:22.901 --> 41:24.567
You're gonna be fine.
You all right?

41:24.651 --> 41:25.692
What, were you in a fight?

41:25.776 --> 41:28.360
[chuckles]
You don't look so good.

41:28.442 --> 41:31.026
You want some water
or something?

41:31.110 --> 41:34.026
[choking]

41:34.110 --> 41:37.360
♪♪♪

41:37.442 --> 41:38.943
Dude!

41:39.026 --> 41:40.609
Stop! Stop!

41:40.692 --> 41:42.901
Get him down! Get him down!
Get him down!

41:42.984 --> 41:44.526
[grunts]

41:44.609 --> 41:48.068
♪♪♪

41:48.151 --> 41:49.901
[Dr. Brogan] I'd like to talk
freely for a minute,

41:49.984 --> 41:51.859
if you don't mind.

41:51.943 --> 41:54.818
You're a severely
traumatized person, Ray.

41:54.901 --> 41:56.567
[Bridget] You blame yourself--

41:56.651 --> 41:58.943
[Dr. Brogan's voice] For the
trauma inflicted on you

41:59.026 --> 42:00.442
by others--
you control it that way.

42:00.526 --> 42:03.360
[Bridget's voice] You make it
your own that way.

42:03.442 --> 42:05.026
I know you know

42:05.110 --> 42:06.484
about post-traumatic stress
disorder, right?

42:06.567 --> 42:08.609
I mean, it's destructive.

42:08.692 --> 42:11.984
And it kills people, okay?
And you have that.

42:12.068 --> 42:13.859
[Dr. Brogan's voice]
And it needs to be treated.

42:13.943 --> 42:15.776
I thought that's what
we were doing here.

42:15.859 --> 42:17.609
[Bridget's voice] These are
things you got to work on

42:17.692 --> 42:18.859
your entire life.

42:18.943 --> 42:21.609
But you need tools
for that, Ray--

42:21.692 --> 42:24.651
group therapy, medication,
one-on-one therapy.

42:24.734 --> 42:27.360
Now, I know you don't want
to hear this right now.

42:27.442 --> 42:30.609
But that's what it takes
to learn how to forgive others

42:30.692 --> 42:33.651
for what they did to you--
to forgive yourself.

42:33.734 --> 42:35.401
Forgive myself for what?

42:35.484 --> 42:37.151
♪♪♪

42:40.984 --> 42:43.193
[distant clatter]

42:43.276 --> 42:46.151
[object sliding]

42:54.318 --> 42:57.276
